The paper proposes a collision detection algorithm for robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm uses Gaussian Process Regression, which is a machine learning technique, indicating a possible fit with the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of kernel structures to model non-linear behaviors, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm is designed to work with joint configurations, which suggests a possible fit with the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions tests performed on a robot, which could indicate a possible fit with the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV) if the tests involved visual data.
